%N A318119 Constant term in the expansion of (Sum_{k=0..n} k*(x^k + x^(-k)))^5.
%H A318119 <a href="/index/Rec#order_10">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (10,-45,120,-210,252,-210,120,-45,10,-1).
%F A318119 a(n) = (n-1) * n * (n+1) * (2*n+1) * (967*n^5+3868*n^4+6005*n^3+5444*n^2+2844*n+1008) / 9072.
%F A318119 From _Elmo R. Oliveira_, Jun 29 2026: (Start)
%F A318119 G.f.: 40*x^2*(1 + x)*(14 + 202*x + 535*x^2 + 202*x^3 + 14*x^4)/(1 - x)^10.
%F A318119 E.g.f.: (1/9072)*x^2*(2540160 + 18990720*x + 35184240*x^2 + 24651648*x^3 + 7733376*x^4 + 1151136*x^5 + 78327*x^6 + 1934*x^7)*exp(x).
%F A318119 a(n) = 10*a(n-1) - 45*a(n-2) + 120*a(n-3) - 210*a(n-4) + 252*a(n-5) - 210*a(n-6) + 120*a(n-7) - 45*a(n-8) + 10*a(n-9) - a(n-10). (End)
%t A318119 a[n_] := Coefficient[Expand[Sum[k * (x^k + x^(-k)), {k, 0, n}]^5], x, 0]; Array[a, 30, 0] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Dec 16 2018 *)
